WEBVTT

00:00:13.260 --> 00:00:14.840
Your nose is bleeding!

00:00:15.010 --> 00:00:16.800
Did you bump into something?!

00:00:17.010 --> 00:00:17.680
Um…

00:00:17.930 --> 00:00:19.010
I don't remember.

00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:21.600
Of course not.

00:00:22.100 --> 00:00:23.350
You're not supposed to.

00:00:24.350 --> 00:00:25.310
Nice to meet you.

00:00:25.810 --> 00:00:27.230
I am Stern Ritter "V,"

00:00:27.270 --> 00:00:31.070
"Vanishing Point" Gwenael Lee.

00:00:31.150 --> 00:00:32.440
STERN RITTER "V" – GWENAEL LEE

00:00:32.860 --> 00:00:35.110
To you, my existence cannot be—

00:00:36.950 --> 00:00:37.990
That's weird…

00:00:38.320 --> 00:00:40.290
I thought I hit him.

00:00:43.160 --> 00:00:44.830
– Yes, that's right…
– Lieutenant Kusajishi!

00:00:44.870 --> 00:00:48.000
My powers are made up of
three versions.

00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:52.710
Version 1: I can erase my form.

00:00:53.090 --> 00:00:56.090
Version 2:
I can erase my existence.

00:00:57.800 --> 00:01:00.640
Whoops.
Her reaction is getting faster.

00:01:01.180 --> 00:01:02.140
In that case…

00:01:03.060 --> 00:01:06.390
Version 3: I will erase
my existence even from your mind.

00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:09.730
Wasn't someone just here?

00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:11.440
Umm…

00:01:25.540 --> 00:01:31.040
Oh, my darling, I don't even know
where my heart has gone

00:01:31.380 --> 00:01:37.010
And I've forgotten
that dream I once had

00:01:37.090 --> 00:01:42.220
Becoming an adult =
keeping a public face and bluffing?

00:01:42.930 --> 00:01:49.100
Tell me, what is reflected
in the painted-over mirror?

00:01:49.770 --> 00:01:54.900
Your photo is starting to fade

00:01:55.440 --> 00:02:00.200
Leaving me, as I change

00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:05.950
I'll shout at the top of my voice
as it pierces through the night

00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:11.750
Burning my chest,
formless fear and all

00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:17.630
It's okay if I can't laugh
like that day

00:02:17.800 --> 00:02:23.470
Sadness, scars, everything…
I want to take them all with me

00:02:24.430 --> 00:02:26.890
You can't kill my vibe, oh baby

00:02:26.890 --> 00:02:29.810
Burning out now,
like a shooting star

00:02:30.230 --> 00:02:32.810
You can't kill my vibe, oh baby

00:02:32.940 --> 00:02:35.530
Burning out now,
like a shooting star

00:02:41.490 --> 00:02:43.990
BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:02.800
Let's try this again.
Nice to meet you.

00:03:04.140 --> 00:03:04.680
Huh?

00:03:05.600 --> 00:03:06.640
I thought I hit him.

00:03:06.810 --> 00:03:08.220
W-What's with this one?!

00:03:08.310 --> 00:03:10.020
She came at me on impulse!

00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:11.940
What do you think you're doing?!

00:03:12.270 --> 00:03:14.440
We don't know yet
if he's a friend or foe.

00:03:14.730 --> 00:03:17.110
Yeah, but I'm pretty sure
he's an enemy.

00:03:17.360 --> 00:03:19.740
I felt a tingle the moment
I saw him.

00:03:19.860 --> 00:03:20.360
Huh?

00:03:20.530 --> 00:03:22.030
She punched me
on pure instinct?!

00:03:22.200 --> 00:03:23.700
Damn animal!

00:03:23.950 --> 00:03:27.830
I was told that it's important
to trust these tingles.

00:03:28.120 --> 00:03:32.670
Tingles that make you feel cold,
hot, or happy…

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:34.000
those kinds!

00:03:35.380 --> 00:03:38.050
Kenny says that
when he finds someone like that,

00:03:38.130 --> 00:03:40.050
he can't resist slaying them.

00:03:40.800 --> 00:03:42.510
But Kenny's not here right now,

00:03:42.550 --> 00:03:46.220
so he won't mind
if I slay this guy, right?

00:03:49.890 --> 00:03:51.060
Die!

00:03:54.270 --> 00:03:55.020
W-What the…?

00:03:55.940 --> 00:03:56.900
Impossible!

00:03:56.940 --> 00:03:58.900
I definitely dodged that sword!

00:03:59.030 --> 00:04:01.570
It couldn't have struck me!
There's just no way!

00:04:01.990 --> 00:04:02.820
You're right.

00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:06.490
My sword strikes its target
whether they dodge it or not.

00:04:06.910 --> 00:04:08.580
What…did you say?

00:04:08.870 --> 00:04:11.620
My sword is a copycat.

00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:15.960
There are copycats on the front
and back of my sword.

00:04:16.420 --> 00:04:18.960
So the more you try to gauge
the distance and timing,

00:04:19.090 --> 00:04:21.010
the more likely you are
to misjudge it and you get hit.

00:04:21.340 --> 00:04:22.970
Okay, come on out…

00:04:23.470 --> 00:04:24.800
Sanpo Kenju.

00:04:26.050 --> 00:04:28.640
W-What the hell is that?!

00:04:31.640 --> 00:04:32.810
Ready? And…

00:04:33.100 --> 00:04:34.980
Hey! Hey!

00:04:34.980 --> 00:04:36.650
Hey!

00:04:37.150 --> 00:04:39.070
– Hey, hey! Hey, hey!
– Th-That's her Shikai…?

00:04:39.900 --> 00:04:41.400
But her sword hasn't changed form.

00:04:42.070 --> 00:04:43.780
It's not even
the materialization

00:04:43.860 --> 00:04:45.240
of the Zanpakuto's true form

00:04:45.280 --> 00:04:46.910
that is said to occur
through Bankai training.

00:04:47.200 --> 00:04:48.910
I didn't know
such a Shikai existed…

00:04:53.080 --> 00:04:53.830
Huh?

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:54.910
That's odd.

00:04:54.960 --> 00:04:57.460
I thought I sliced you in half.

00:04:57.710 --> 00:04:58.580
Fool!

00:04:58.750 --> 00:05:00.340
Did you think I wouldn't
be able to dodge it

00:05:00.420 --> 00:05:01.920
after you revealed how it works?!

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:09.140
This can't be happening…

00:05:09.350 --> 00:05:10.310
Oh, but it is.

00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:15.230
When did you
get inside the barrier?!

00:05:15.690 --> 00:05:16.440
No way…

00:05:16.980 --> 00:05:19.650
I fought really well, didn't I?

00:05:19.940 --> 00:05:22.400
Yeah, you really did…

00:05:23.070 --> 00:05:26.030
for a product of my imagination.

00:05:26.900 --> 00:05:27.740
Wait…

00:05:27.950 --> 00:05:30.950
With my powers,
these guys would be no—

00:05:31.080 --> 00:05:32.910
Yes, your powers are amazing.

00:05:33.370 --> 00:05:35.790
I mean,
you can erase your existence

00:05:35.790 --> 00:05:38.250
from sight, mind, and memory.

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:39.920
See?
That's why…

00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:44.130
you just disappeared
from my memory.

00:05:47.010 --> 00:05:50.090
Gremmy!

00:05:50.390 --> 00:05:51.220
I'm sorry.

00:05:51.850 --> 00:05:54.100
I can no longer imagine
a future for you.

00:05:58.770 --> 00:06:00.690
Just who are you?

00:06:00.980 --> 00:06:02.610
Please step away from there…

00:06:02.940 --> 00:06:04.570
Are you worried
about these captains?

00:06:04.610 --> 00:06:05.400
Now!

00:06:06.070 --> 00:06:07.280
Don't worry.

00:06:08.570 --> 00:06:09.530
I already killed them.

00:06:10.160 --> 00:06:10.910
No…

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:20.000
Huh?

00:06:20.040 --> 00:06:20.960
My arm…

00:06:22.380 --> 00:06:23.540
Imagine this…

00:06:24.380 --> 00:06:26.050
What would happen
if the bone in your arm

00:06:26.090 --> 00:06:27.550
was made of cookies?

00:06:28.420 --> 00:06:31.010
Just now, you thought,
"it would naturally break apart," right?

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:33.890
This is what you imagined next…

00:06:34.140 --> 00:06:35.890
"If the bone in my arm
was made of cookies,"

00:06:36.020 --> 00:06:39.020
"then maybe the rest of my bones
are cookies, too."

00:06:42.020 --> 00:06:43.440
In this world,

00:06:43.650 --> 00:06:46.480
the greatest power of all
is the power of imagination.

00:06:47.070 --> 00:06:49.070
Everything I imagine…

00:06:49.700 --> 00:06:52.160
becomes reality.

00:06:57.410 --> 00:06:58.750
What is this?

00:06:59.040 --> 00:07:02.040
I came looking for Yachiru

00:07:02.040 --> 00:07:03.960
because her Spiritual Pressure
felt wobbly,

00:07:04.130 --> 00:07:07.090
but all I find is a kid acting up.

00:07:09.050 --> 00:07:09.970
Kenny…!

00:07:13.930 --> 00:07:15.390
C-Captain Zaraki…

00:07:15.850 --> 00:07:16.930
U-Um…

00:07:17.640 --> 00:07:19.480
Captain Unohana…is she…?

00:07:24.230 --> 00:07:25.310
She's dead.

00:07:29.570 --> 00:07:32.070
I…see…

00:07:35.120 --> 00:07:36.910
I killed her.

00:07:37.410 --> 00:07:40.290
If you hate me for it,
you can go ahead and kill me.

00:07:42.080 --> 00:07:42.920
Thank goodness…

00:07:43.710 --> 00:07:48.130
The fact that you killed her
means you've succeeded it…

00:07:49.590 --> 00:07:52.090
…Captain Unohana's title.

00:07:52.800 --> 00:07:54.890
Yeah, I did.

00:07:55.010 --> 00:07:56.390
Hmm…

00:07:56.930 --> 00:07:59.060
So this is Kenpachi Zaraki, huh?

00:08:00.060 --> 00:08:01.060
You seem strong.

00:08:02.020 --> 00:08:03.900
You're just as I imagined.

00:08:09.150 --> 00:08:10.070
No!

00:08:15.160 --> 00:08:19.990
POST INVASION – SEIREITEI STONE FORT

00:08:19.120 --> 00:08:19.990
Okay.

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:21.790
I've set the stage for you.

00:08:22.080 --> 00:08:24.330
After all,
you're the famous Kenpachi Zaraki.

00:08:24.750 --> 00:08:27.380
It would be rude not to
welcome you on a grand stage.

00:08:27.920 --> 00:08:29.130
What is all this?

00:08:29.130 --> 00:08:31.050
Some kind of spell?

00:08:31.050 --> 00:08:33.510
It's neither a spell
nor an illusion.

00:08:33.670 --> 00:08:34.930
It's reality.

00:08:35.220 --> 00:08:39.140
I am Gremmy, "The Visionary"
who turns fantasy into reality.

00:08:39.390 --> 00:08:40.850
STERN RITTER "V" –
GREMMY THOUMEAUX

00:08:41.060 --> 00:08:43.940
I think you're lucky
to be able to fight me…

00:08:44.810 --> 00:08:48.400
because I think I am the strongest
of the Stern Ritters.

00:08:49.690 --> 00:08:51.030
That so?

00:08:52.610 --> 00:08:54.070
I'll say it again…

00:08:54.780 --> 00:08:57.240
I can turn fantasy into reality.

00:08:57.700 --> 00:08:58.950
See what I did just now?

00:08:59.080 --> 00:09:00.540
I simply imagined that

00:09:00.620 --> 00:09:04.620
my body was far stronger
than steel, and…

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:09.880
Come on…

00:09:10.420 --> 00:09:13.550
If you're as hard as steel,
then you should've said so.

00:09:13.840 --> 00:09:15.930
I would have just cut you
as if I was cutting steel

00:09:16.010 --> 00:09:17.130
from the very beginning.

00:09:18.890 --> 00:09:20.600
What's with the face?

00:09:21.140 --> 00:09:23.100
Did you imagine that
I couldn't cut you?

00:09:24.060 --> 00:09:25.270
Let me tell you something…

00:09:26.100 --> 00:09:28.690
Your puny imagination

00:09:28.770 --> 00:09:31.320
can't create anything
that I can't cut.

00:09:32.190 --> 00:09:33.320
You know why?

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:35.990
Because I'm Kenpachi.

00:10:00.720 --> 00:10:01.930
What is that thing?

00:10:02.390 --> 00:10:04.100
What is going on?!

00:10:06.230 --> 00:10:08.140
H-Hey…
This Spiritual Pressure…

00:10:09.770 --> 00:10:10.940
It's Captain Zaraki!

00:10:12.150 --> 00:10:14.110
– It's getting noisy down there…
– Captain Zaraki…

00:10:14.110 --> 00:10:15.530
– It's getting noisy down there…
– Captain Zaraki is here!

00:10:15.780 --> 00:10:16.990
– Let them be.
– Now we can win this war!

00:10:17.070 --> 00:10:19.950
They think they can win the war
now that you're here.

00:10:20.240 --> 00:10:21.950
They're free to imagine that.

00:10:22.870 --> 00:10:25.040
You can heal your own wounds?

00:10:25.620 --> 00:10:26.500
I can?

00:10:27.200 --> 00:10:27.870
I guess you're right.

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:30.170
But all I did…

00:10:30.880 --> 00:10:35.340
was imagine that my sword wound
had already healed.

00:10:37.090 --> 00:10:40.430
My power probably sounds like
a bad joke to you, doesn't it?

00:10:41.140 --> 00:10:46.520
People like you cannot understand
my power until you lose.

00:10:47.020 --> 00:10:50.770
So come at me, Kenpachi Zaraki.

00:10:51.150 --> 00:10:53.310
I won't say I'll take you on
with just a finger

00:10:53.360 --> 00:10:55.020
or anything corny like that.

00:10:55.610 --> 00:10:58.070
I won't use even a single finger.

00:10:58.320 --> 00:11:01.910
I'll kill you using only
what's inside my head.

00:11:03.700 --> 00:11:05.080
Your powers are ridiculous.

00:11:05.330 --> 00:11:05.870
But…

00:11:05.910 --> 00:11:09.250
I don't mind fighting against
something that's beyond reason!

00:11:11.210 --> 00:11:13.580
What're you doing, Yachiru?
Take cover!

00:11:13.880 --> 00:11:15.590
Don't be so hard on her.

00:11:15.880 --> 00:11:17.550
Right now, because of my power,

00:11:17.590 --> 00:11:20.220
every bone in her body
is made of cookies.

00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:22.800
What the hell is a "cookie"?

00:11:23.050 --> 00:11:24.430
You don't know what it is?

00:11:24.640 --> 00:11:27.010
Maybe I should've gone with
Rakugan or something.

00:11:27.560 --> 00:11:28.810
Rakugan, huh?

00:11:29.020 --> 00:11:31.020
Then why didn't you just say so?

00:11:31.480 --> 00:11:33.770
You sure do
beat around the bush!

00:11:39.400 --> 00:11:41.070
Pretty absurd, isn't it?

00:11:41.490 --> 00:11:45.200
The air you jumped up into
was already underwater.

00:11:53.920 --> 00:11:56.880
Now die a slow death,

00:11:56.880 --> 00:12:00.050
surrounded by water and crushed
by the cracks in the earth.

00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:02.590
No matter what kind of
monster you are,

00:12:02.720 --> 00:12:04.930
one hour should be plenty.

00:12:11.930 --> 00:12:15.020
Seems like Yachiru's bones
are back to normal.

00:12:15.900 --> 00:12:17.900
Were you so desperate to beat me

00:12:18.110 --> 00:12:20.820
that you couldn't use your mind
on Yachiru?

00:12:25.950 --> 00:12:27.490
Sheesh…

00:12:27.660 --> 00:12:29.120
You know,

00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:31.000
the world speaks badly of those

00:12:31.080 --> 00:12:32.960
who cannot do anything
more than imagine.

00:12:33.460 --> 00:12:34.960
But when you see someone

00:12:34.960 --> 00:12:36.920
who can do anything
with just their imagination…

00:12:36.960 --> 00:12:39.170
it makes you realize
just how peaceful it was

00:12:39.340 --> 00:12:41.010
when they couldn't do anything.

00:12:42.380 --> 00:12:44.470
Kotetsu's Spiritual Pressure
is still present.

00:12:44.970 --> 00:12:46.840
Go down and get your arm fixed.

00:12:47.010 --> 00:12:47.850
Okay!

00:12:50.890 --> 00:12:53.140
What is it you want to do with me?

00:12:53.930 --> 00:12:55.480
You want to fight, right?

00:12:56.400 --> 00:12:57.440
Fight…?

00:12:57.940 --> 00:12:59.940
What was it you called yourself?

00:13:01.110 --> 00:13:03.110
Aren't you the strongest Quincy?

00:13:03.780 --> 00:13:04.820
If you're the strongest,

00:13:04.990 --> 00:13:07.950
don't you want to crush
the strongest?

00:13:08.160 --> 00:13:09.160
So come on!

00:13:09.200 --> 00:13:10.870
Let's start the battle.

00:13:11.120 --> 00:13:14.000
You can't call it a real battle
if you're distracted by someone

00:13:14.040 --> 00:13:16.000
other than the enemy
right in front of you,

00:13:16.170 --> 00:13:17.210
now would you?!

00:13:20.540 --> 00:13:21.590
What was that?

00:13:25.300 --> 00:13:27.180
What did this guy just say?

00:13:27.890 --> 00:13:28.930
"If you're the strongest,"

00:13:29.010 --> 00:13:30.970
"don't you want to crush
the strongest?"

00:13:31.850 --> 00:13:33.850
I never thought of
something like that.

00:13:34.640 --> 00:13:38.190
Nobody ever tried to
lay a finger on me.

00:13:38.940 --> 00:13:40.860
Because it's obvious.

00:13:40.900 --> 00:13:43.150
It's obvious that
I'm the strongest.

00:13:43.610 --> 00:13:45.190
That's why…

00:13:46.030 --> 00:13:49.280
there's no need for me
to prove it by killing somebody.

00:13:49.910 --> 00:13:53.200
That's why I've never felt
the desire to crush anyone.

00:13:54.160 --> 00:13:57.040
So then, why…?

00:13:57.580 --> 00:13:58.920
Why do I want to…

00:13:59.500 --> 00:14:02.460
…crush this guy so badly?!

00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:19.020
You used…

00:14:20.600 --> 00:14:21.610
your hands.

00:14:23.520 --> 00:14:24.820
That's a good look.

00:14:25.230 --> 00:14:28.240
Looks like this thing is
finally going to have some fun.

00:14:28.950 --> 00:14:30.110
"A good look"?

00:14:31.700 --> 00:14:34.370
I don't know
how I look right now,

00:14:35.620 --> 00:14:36.750
but it's strange…

00:14:37.250 --> 00:14:39.080
Why do I…

00:14:39.540 --> 00:14:41.420
Why do I feel so…

00:14:41.920 --> 00:14:43.340
good right now?!

00:14:50.300 --> 00:14:51.680
That was lame…

00:14:51.970 --> 00:14:54.930
I thought I told you,
I can cut through even steel!

00:14:56.430 --> 00:14:57.310
I can't pull it out!

00:15:01.230 --> 00:15:02.690
That was lame…

00:15:02.900 --> 00:15:05.860
I thought I told you,
cutting me is useless.

00:15:07.780 --> 00:15:08.570
Crap…!

00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:12.280
Too slow!

00:15:12.780 --> 00:15:14.910
I realized too late
that I had been cut!

00:15:15.410 --> 00:15:16.910
In that momentary lapse,

00:15:17.080 --> 00:15:19.040
I will be struck by
his next blow!

00:15:24.340 --> 00:15:25.040
No way…

00:15:25.880 --> 00:15:27.800
Why can't I stop his sword?

00:15:28.340 --> 00:15:30.760
Am I really going to lose
to this guy?

00:15:31.300 --> 00:15:32.680
This can't be happening…
This can't be happening…

00:15:32.720 --> 00:15:33.890
This can't be happening…

00:15:33.930 --> 00:15:35.550
This can't be happening!

00:15:36.760 --> 00:15:37.680
What's wrong?

00:15:41.270 --> 00:15:44.150
Did you imagine yourself losing?

00:15:44.900 --> 00:15:46.110
He's right…

00:15:50.280 --> 00:15:51.320
Thank you.

00:15:52.070 --> 00:15:53.240
For what?

00:15:54.030 --> 00:15:57.120
I was able to completely wipe away
any thoughts of my death

00:15:57.160 --> 00:15:59.080
thanks to your words.

00:15:59.540 --> 00:16:02.000
I can no longer die.

00:16:02.790 --> 00:16:03.960
You'll regret this.

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:06.090
I never did!

00:16:08.210 --> 00:16:10.050
Let me return the favor…

00:16:10.050 --> 00:16:12.760
by showing you my greatest power.

00:16:12.970 --> 00:16:14.130
Is that a doppelganger?

00:16:14.390 --> 00:16:15.680
It's not a doppelganger.

00:16:15.890 --> 00:16:19.390
I can even create life
with my imagination.

00:16:21.270 --> 00:16:22.770
Neither of us can be cut.

00:16:23.440 --> 00:16:25.150
Neither of us will die.

00:16:25.520 --> 00:16:26.400
And…

00:16:26.940 --> 00:16:27.820
– the power of
– the power of

00:16:27.860 --> 00:16:28.690
– my imagination
– my imagination

00:16:28.860 --> 00:16:30.570
– simply doubles.
– simply doubles.

00:16:33.320 --> 00:16:34.910
What the hell is that?

00:16:34.910 --> 00:16:36.450
A meteor.

00:16:36.820 --> 00:16:39.370
You can disappear along with
the Seireitei itself.

00:16:39.830 --> 00:16:42.870
I will be the only one
who survives among the rubble.

00:16:43.040 --> 00:16:44.710
A meteor?

00:16:44.960 --> 00:16:47.580
I've never cut one of those before.

00:16:48.130 --> 00:16:51.590
Isn't this exciting, Nozarashi?

00:16:54.970 --> 00:16:56.180
W-We're doomed…

00:16:56.220 --> 00:16:57.590
It's coming down on us!

00:16:57.640 --> 00:16:58.890
We're going to die…!

00:16:59.100 --> 00:17:00.600
We're all going to die!

00:17:00.850 --> 00:17:03.270
Let's just say, for example,

00:17:03.560 --> 00:17:06.270
that it isn't just my imagination…

00:17:07.270 --> 00:17:10.610
Suppose you managed to kill me
right now.

00:17:11.070 --> 00:17:12.070
It would be useless.

00:17:12.280 --> 00:17:15.400
The meteor is already a reality—
it won't go away.

00:17:15.530 --> 00:17:17.950
It'll fall and wipe everybody out.

00:17:17.950 --> 00:17:21.580
I'll be the only one alive,
just as I imagined.

00:17:22.080 --> 00:17:25.410
You see? There's nothing
you can do about it…

00:17:25.750 --> 00:17:27.210
Kenpachi Zaraki.

00:17:29.420 --> 00:17:31.130
"Nothing you can do about it"?

00:17:31.800 --> 00:17:34.970
Sure. Maybe for you.

00:17:40.850 --> 00:17:41.720
Drink…

00:17:42.140 --> 00:17:43.600
Nozarashi!

00:17:50.020 --> 00:17:52.070
Where'd you come from, kid?

00:17:56.950 --> 00:17:59.110
Hey, kid…
What's your name?

00:18:01.370 --> 00:18:02.620
You don't have one?

00:18:03.910 --> 00:18:05.000
Neither do I.

00:18:37.990 --> 00:18:40.160
You damn monster!

00:18:40.280 --> 00:18:41.370
Calm down.

00:18:41.660 --> 00:18:43.120
It's simple, really.

00:18:44.120 --> 00:18:46.540
There is nothing I cannot cut.

00:18:47.540 --> 00:18:48.790
You're right…

00:18:49.290 --> 00:18:50.960
That is simple.

00:18:53.090 --> 00:18:55.550
Increasing your numbers…

00:18:55.670 --> 00:18:57.970
won't change a thing!

00:18:57.970 --> 00:18:59.010
It will.

00:18:59.470 --> 00:19:03.140
If there is nothing you cannot cut,
then I will kill you with…

00:19:03.430 --> 00:19:05.060
…something without form!

00:19:05.930 --> 00:19:08.930
Die in the vacuum of outer space!

00:19:09.980 --> 00:19:11.230
In the vacuum of space,

00:19:11.310 --> 00:19:15.150
your body fluids evaporate
and your blood begins to boil.

00:19:15.650 --> 00:19:18.740
Your bodily tissues will collapse
and you'll die a slow death.

00:19:19.030 --> 00:19:21.450
That is, of course,
if you remain conscious until then.

00:19:21.910 --> 00:19:22.700
What—?!

00:19:23.160 --> 00:19:24.160
What's wrong?

00:19:25.370 --> 00:19:27.080
You forgot to…

00:19:27.410 --> 00:19:28.790
harden your body.

00:19:33.670 --> 00:19:34.250
What's that?

00:19:54.400 --> 00:19:55.560
What the hell?

00:19:56.110 --> 00:19:57.860
You really are a monster.

00:19:58.280 --> 00:19:59.110
Fine…

00:19:59.860 --> 00:20:00.690
In that case,

00:20:00.740 --> 00:20:03.860
I'll just have to become
stronger than you!

00:20:04.410 --> 00:20:05.700
I want to win…
I want to win…

00:20:05.740 --> 00:20:07.120
I want to win…
I want to win!

00:20:07.450 --> 00:20:10.040
For the first time in my life,
I want to beat someone.

00:20:10.370 --> 00:20:14.170
I will crush you
and prove my strength!

00:20:14.670 --> 00:20:17.090
To you!

00:20:22.970 --> 00:20:27.350
You turned me into a monster
inside your own head.

00:20:28.850 --> 00:20:31.060
That same monster
is what just killed you.

00:20:32.730 --> 00:20:34.270
You stupid fool…

00:20:47.160 --> 00:20:51.450
All at once, the lights went out

00:20:51.580 --> 00:20:52.790
Reminding me

00:20:52.870 --> 00:20:54.040
with a voice

00:20:54.080 --> 00:20:56.040
and I cannot move

00:20:56.960 --> 00:21:01.170
Unable to convey even a millimeter

00:21:01.340 --> 00:21:03.760
of the lines that I dubbed

00:21:03.800 --> 00:21:06.010
All lines
that I don't want to forget

00:21:06.090 --> 00:21:07.430
Rewound

00:21:07.470 --> 00:21:08.510
Repeated

00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:09.640
Became a mark

00:21:09.680 --> 00:21:10.890
And I notice the dust

00:21:10.970 --> 00:21:12.100
I wait and wait

00:21:12.180 --> 00:21:13.600
But it won't start

00:21:13.680 --> 00:21:14.730
If it's already ended

00:21:14.810 --> 00:21:15.980
I give up

00:21:15.980 --> 00:21:17.190
But can I

00:21:17.230 --> 00:21:18.440
borrow your shoulder?

00:21:18.440 --> 00:21:20.020
With that knife

00:21:20.150 --> 00:21:22.070
that was left behind

00:21:23.110 --> 00:21:25.070
Pierce it through

00:21:25.110 --> 00:21:26.360
Still

00:21:26.490 --> 00:21:28.700
in the middle of a dream,

00:21:28.780 --> 00:21:31.160
We kept searching

00:21:31.330 --> 00:21:33.370
For the scar that

00:21:33.540 --> 00:21:36.120
the revolving world remembers

00:21:36.210 --> 00:21:38.330
With just the strong desire

00:21:38.460 --> 00:21:41.710
to keep on living

00:21:41.880 --> 00:21:46.880
We'll choose a tomorrow
that will not return

00:21:47.010 --> 00:21:51.640
In just a little while

00:21:51.680 --> 00:21:55.980
The final curtain will fall

00:21:56.810 --> 00:22:00.310
Shining upon us

00:22:00.440 --> 00:22:03.320
The blurred end roll

00:22:15.080 --> 00:22:18.750
Was I killed by
my own imagination?

00:22:20.420 --> 00:22:21.920
No, that's not it.

00:22:31.180 --> 00:22:33.180
No, Kenpachi Zaraki.

00:22:34.100 --> 00:22:36.350
My imagination was correct.

00:22:37.600 --> 00:22:39.020
Too correct, in fact.

00:22:39.940 --> 00:22:44.150
I was able to correctly imagine
all of your powers.

00:22:45.110 --> 00:22:46.190
But the one thing…

00:22:46.860 --> 00:22:48.860
I couldn't imagine correctly

00:22:49.860 --> 00:22:54.910
was that only your body
can withstand your powers.

00:22:56.580 --> 00:22:59.830
It wasn't my power of imagination
that lost to you.

00:23:00.040 --> 00:23:01.250
It was this body of mine.

00:23:02.250 --> 00:23:04.170
No, that is an excuse, isn't it?

00:23:04.880 --> 00:23:06.960
Aw…damn it…

00:23:08.380 --> 00:23:10.010
I wanted to win so badly…!

00:23:16.390 --> 00:23:18.350
What the hell…is that?

00:23:18.930 --> 00:23:20.020
I told you.

00:23:20.770 --> 00:23:25.150
I would kill you
without using a single finger.

00:23:25.980 --> 00:23:30.070
Even this body of mine
is all a product of my imagination.

00:23:31.070 --> 00:23:32.490
Exactly like I said…

00:23:32.740 --> 00:23:36.410
I didn't use a single finger
against you.

00:23:37.240 --> 00:23:40.330
Although I was the one who died.

00:23:42.000 --> 00:23:42.580
Ah…

00:23:43.080 --> 00:23:46.460
Seems like my imagination
is at its limit…

00:23:47.920 --> 00:23:49.130
It's going to be sad…

00:23:50.010 --> 00:23:51.800
imagining what lies ahead,

00:23:51.880 --> 00:23:55.760
a world where I can no longer
imagine anything.

00:24:11.530 --> 00:24:14.870
"Struck by thunder,
you're on your knees."

00:24:15.740 --> 00:24:16.990
"That is my desire."

